   Today I reached a decision. Effective today i am cancelling my account. I know everyone says they are sorry etc... etc..., so instead of laying on the same BS im just gonna give the cold clear truth so this is kinda a rant lol (though really this has nothing to do with anything u guys have done). I want a chance before i move on to say what i have been thinking for a long time and only now truly apreciate. EVERQUEST IS A GAME! A GAME A GAME A GAME A GAME. Ok now that that is clear let me continue. I am quiting because now that i have started working and have all this other stuff going in my life it all seems so petty.<br>
   <br>
Not that i dont enjoy games anymore or anything i still very much do, and anime and manga and playing my trumpet (though i have considerably less time to do any of those things). Its just that when i see a man who is married and has grandkids, but is also the leader of a guild and spends hours surfing message boards and writing long rants when Verant does soemthing i just have to think to myself, what is wrong with that person that a game is so important. Now this may offend some of you, which is good cuz anything u say will always offend someone or else its not worth saying. I mean 2 months of working and other responsibilities and i feel like its just not worth getting worked up over such a thing as a reduction of solo exp.<br>
   <br>
Now i am not just quiting because of that. The true main reason is time. No matter what they say EQ is not for a casual gamer. EQ is for my little bro who is 12 and has tons of free time. He has a level 60 and im very glad he enjoys the game.<br>
   <br>
So yes i am quiting and again this has nothing to do with any of you it just has to do with the game, i dont have the time or the will or the energy to deal with everquest and the small amount of fun isnt worth the headache. So i must say goodbye, it has been great meeting u all. This is Raveloe Crimsonblade signing off and retiring. <br>
<br>
Later guys and gals<br>
